Hey, sometimes, putting

285
00:13:23,524 --> 00:13:25,156
some distance in relationships

286
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,960
can deepen the bond, you know?

287
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:30,480
Yes, like helping to choose a dish.

288
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,780
What are you saying?

289
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:41,840
What do you think you're doing?

290
00:13:45,130 --> 00:13:47,750
Why would you lie about that?

291
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:50,192
Geez, what is it?

292
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:52,723
Yeah, I know. You're mad about that?

293
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:55,630
- I'm gonna beat you to a pulp!
- There's nothing to be angry about.

294
00:13:55,630 --> 00:13:58,240
Hey, hey, let's calm down for a moment.

295
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:01,430
What? You stay out of this!

296
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,290
You want a piece of me?

297
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:07,860
- Wait, wait. Let's break up.
- Huh?

298
00:14:15,820 --> 00:14:16,510
Huh?

299
00:14:31,490 --> 00:14:33,030
We managed to escape.

300
00:14:36,610 --> 00:14:40,090
Hey, who was that guy?

301
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:43,593
That guy back there...

302
00:14:43,618 --> 00:14:44,866
he was my boyfriend.

303
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,070
Your boyfriend?

304
00:14:47,830 --> 00:14:50,150
Well, ex now.

305
00:14:51,220 --> 00:14:53,240
He found out I was two-timing him.

306
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:57,800
Huh? Isn't that your fault?

307
00:15:03,260 --> 00:15:04,190
I'm hungry.

308
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,190
I need something to eat.

309
00:15:14,890 --> 00:15:16,090
So, you're a chef, huh?

310
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,790
Running the place all by yourself.

311
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:27,060
No.

312
00:15:28,307 --> 00:15:28,860
Huh?

313
00:15:29,990 --> 00:15:31,600
My mom passed away from illness,

314
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,990
so I took over.

315
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:36,890
But I can't replicate her flavors,

316
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,480
and customers are leaving.

317
00:15:43,570 --> 00:15:45,600
The appearance is not a problem.

318
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:47,940
Information is everything.

319
00:15:52,450 --> 00:15:53,790
It can't be helped.

320
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,280
I guess I'll help out.

321
00:15:56,890 --> 00:15:57,490
Huh?

322
00:15:58,270 --> 00:16:00,610
Since I got kicked out of my ex's place.

323
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,520
Please let me live and work here.

324
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:07,900
Can you even cook?

325
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:09,600
Nope, but

326
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:13,060
whatever you can't do, I can do it.

327
00:16:22,450 --> 00:16:23,380
Oww.

328
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:26,040
It's Soga-san.

329
00:16:29,050 --> 00:16:29,780
Hello.

330
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,090
Oh, hello, Sakae-kun.

331
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,940
I'm truly sorry.

332
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,800
I couldn't do anything after all.

333
00:16:37,790 --> 00:16:38,620
That's okay.

334
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:41,990
After all, our guest came back.

335
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:43,650
So, you know.

336
00:16:45,069 --> 00:16:47,633
How about I treat you to a meal

337
00:16:47,658 --> 00:16:49,391
as a way of apologizing?

338
00:16:50,210 --> 00:16:53,000
You don't need to go to that trouble.

339
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:54,890
No, it's not just about that.

340
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:01,650
I also want to see your face, Sakae-kun.

341
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:07,220
And there are some

342
00:17:08,210 --> 00:17:10,280
important things we need to discuss.

343
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:15,470
Isn't your work a lot?

344
00:17:15,810 --> 00:17:17,400
I'll definitely manage it somehow!

345
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:20,010
So, what do you say?

346
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:21,990
I got it.

347
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:25,300
Shall we go then?

348
00:17:25,987 --> 00:17:27,420
Yes, thank you.

349
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:41,830
- Still alive, huh?
- Wow, Okawara-san is so strong.

350
00:17:41,830 --> 00:17:44,130
- Can you please review this by today?
- Yes, I understand.

351
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:45,220
Sorry for the trouble.

352
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,310
Alright.

353
00:17:57,310 --> 00:18:00,990
(Let's meet at seven PM tomorrow!)

354
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:10,580
This is the progress so far, sir.

355
00:18:10,580 --> 00:18:12,265
Wow, as expected, the progress

356
00:18:12,289 --> 00:18:13,809
has been very fast!

357
00:18:13,950 --> 00:18:15,360
Alright, starting tomorrow,

358
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:16,524
I want one of you guys

359
00:18:16,532 --> 00:18:17,703
to take a lead role.

360
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:19,020
Me too!

361
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:22,600
- Well then, I'll take my leave.
- Yeah, thanks for your hard work.

362
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:23,950
- Thanks for your hard work.
- Yes.

363
00:18:25,510 --> 00:18:26,050
Umm...

364
00:18:29,470 --> 00:18:30,980
The quotation is due today?

365
00:18:33,630 --> 00:18:34,570
I'm sorry.

366
00:18:35,370 --> 00:18:36,355
I thought it was due

367
00:18:36,380 --> 00:18:37,668
by the end of this week.

368
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:40,950
- I'll ask them to wait a little longer.
- Oh, please no.

369
00:18:41,575 --> 00:18:42,330
You see...

370
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:45,411
I kind of pressed them about their

371
00:18:45,427 --> 00:18:47,285
slow response on the phone yesterday.

372
00:18:47,310 --> 00:18:47,950
Huh?

373
00:18:48,599 --> 00:18:51,630
Given that, we can't afford to delay.

374
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:59,280
For now, just wait at the office.

375
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:00,390
I'm sorry.

376
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,780
Yes, yes.

377
00:19:12,970 --> 00:19:13,760
You see...

378
00:19:14,910 --> 00:19:16,050
Work stuff?

379
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:18,660
Yes.

380
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:21,030
Got it!

381
00:19:22,110 --> 00:19:23,599
No problem at all!

382
00:19:24,318 --> 00:19:25,758
So please take your time.

383
00:19:27,385 --> 00:19:28,315
I'm sorry.

384
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:31,020
Yes. Maybe next time.

385
00:19:45,470 --> 00:19:48,580
Oh, what a relief.

386
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:51,530
- Good, you're still here.
- What?

387
00:19:52,270 --> 00:19:53,527
I heard you had a date

388
00:19:53,552 --> 00:19:55,072
from Kaname today,

389
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,277
so I came to see what kind

390
00:19:56,301 --> 00:19:57,355
of face you're making.

391
00:19:58,760 --> 00:19:59,420
I see.

392
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,550
Huh? What's with that expression?

393
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:07,490
Did he cancel on you?

394
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:12,610
Man, that's harsh, Soga-san.

395
00:20:13,177 --> 00:20:14,337
It's not Soga-san's fault.

396
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,020
How could you not feel hurt?

397
00:20:19,710 --> 00:20:22,050
An ex being treated badly.

398
00:20:29,370 --> 00:20:30,750
What can I say?

399
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:36,220
In the past...

400
00:20:37,835 --> 00:20:38,765
I've always thought that I,

401
00:20:38,790 --> 00:20:39,735
a human being, had to live alone.

402
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:42,300
- What's with all this sudden talk?
- Come on, listen up.

403
00:20:43,890 --> 00:20:45,270
That's why I don't want to

404
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:49,560
get too deep into love.

405
00:20:51,930 --> 00:20:53,101
As soon as I start

406
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:54,859
seeing each other's flaws,

407
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,460
we break up casually.

408
00:20:59,300 --> 00:20:59,980
But still,

409
00:21:04,140 --> 00:21:05,730
you're special.

410
00:21:09,140 --> 00:21:10,655
No matter how selfish I am,

411
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,218
you never get tired of me.

412
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:14,843
Whenever I'm in trouble,

413
00:21:14,868 --> 00:21:16,116
you're always there

414
00:21:16,141 --> 00:21:17,405
to help me overcome it.

415
00:21:18,490 --> 00:21:20,630
It's a shame for me

416
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:22,520
and I also feel guilty.

417
00:21:23,850 --> 00:21:25,180
I'm afraid that my life

418
00:21:26,890 --> 00:21:28,225
and other people's lives

419
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,265
will get mixed up.

420
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:33,470
All those feelings kept growing, and I

421
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,180
ended up running away from you.

422
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,260
Even so,

423
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:43,780
maybe there were other options.

424
00:21:50,670 --> 00:21:52,370
- The me right now...
- I understand.

425
00:21:53,870 --> 00:21:55,560
It doesn't have to be me.

426
00:21:57,710 --> 00:21:58,470
But...

427
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:02,580
because you're special to me...

428
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:06,430
I just want you to be happy.

429
00:22:16,530 --> 00:22:17,810
I understand you

430
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:21,330
better than Soga-san does.

431
00:22:44,130 --> 00:22:45,100
Sorry for the wait.

432
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:10,690
(Next episode)

433
00:23:10,690 --> 00:23:11,980
I won't back off.

434
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:14,960
(The wall of Tokyo that separates them)
In one year I will return to Tokyo.

435
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:16,600
(Declaring War and Laying Siege to the Love Fortress in Osaka)
Sakae is mine.

436
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,100
Mind your own business.

437
00:23:18,530 --> 00:23:20,710
(what will their destiny be like?)
Perhaps it's called destiny.

438
00:23:20,710 --> 00:23:22,500
Being just friends,

439
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:23,670
is alright, right?
